# Project: Cryptocurrency Portfolio Management App

## Technology Stack
- Next.js for frontend and server-side rendering
- Payload CMS for content management

## Code Style
- Use ESLint for JavaScript/TypeScript linting
- Use Prettier for code formatting
- Follow AirBnB JavaScript Style Guide

## Git Practices
- Use feature branches for development
- Write clear, concise commit messages
- Squash commits before merging to main branch

## Testing
- Write unit tests for all components and functions
- Aim for at least 80% code coverage

## Documentation
- Document all major functions and components
- Keep FURPS.md and what-is-this.md up to date
- Document API endpoints and data models

## Security
- Follow OWASP security guidelines
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Encrypt sensitive data, especially related to cryptocurrency keys and addresses

## Performance
- Optimize for fast loading times
- Implement efficient data fetching and caching strategies

## Accessibility
- Follow WCAG 2.1 guidelines
- Ensure the app is usable with keyboard navigation

## Responsive Design
- Ensure the app works well on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices

## Version Control
- Use semantic versioning (SemVer) for releases

## Deployment
- Set up CI/CD pipeline for automated testing and deployment
- Use environment variables for configuration

## Maintenance
- Regularly update dependencies
- Monitor and address technical debt
